                     "topFinding":  "The god-file decomposition landed and it is real: all six tracked files are under 1000 lines and the ratchet in scripts/.bp_baseline.json matches disk exactly. What did not land is everything downstream of it. docs/ARCHITECTURE.md is stamped v0.59.27 and still says hud.gd is \"down to 1918 lines\" (it is 905); docs/GODOT_BEST_PRACTICES_ADHERENCE.md still describes gameplay.gd as a 3414-line god-object in the present tense. Both are docs CLAUDE.md names as authoritative. Meanwhile the ratchet only guards the six files it was pointed at, so source/buildings/building.gd (1152 lines) is now the largest script in the tree and nothing stops it growing. The campaign moved the code and left its own map behind. Add to that four days of silence since v0.59.34, a docs-only release, and a completion field that still reads 50% with an empty remaining[], and the honest read is that BR finished its refactor runway and has not decided what to do next.",
